# Feature: Arrival Brief

## What It Is
An LLM-generated personalized 1-page briefing shown in-app 48 hours before check-in.
Zero associate involvement. Opt-in consent toggle in user profile.

## Data Inputs
| Section | Source for Demo | Production Source |
|---|---|---|
| Weather | OpenWeatherMap API (LIVE, free) | Same |
| Events | Mock JSON in seed data | Ticketmaster Discovery API |
| Dining | Mock JSON filtered by dietary prefs | Opera PMS F&B data + partner DB |
| Transit | Mock static data per city | Google Maps Directions API |
| Property notes | Mock per hotel | Opera PMS / GXP guest notes |
| Sunrise/sunset | Open-Meteo API (LIVE, free) | Same |

## LLM Prompt Template
Keep this consistent — do not change prompt structure without updating this rule.

```
System: You are a warm, knowledgeable Marriott concierge.
Generate a concise arrival brief for a guest.

Guest preferences: {dietary_prefs}, {interest_tags}
Hotel: {hotel_name}, {city}
Stay: {check_in} to {check_out}
Weather: {weather_json}
Events (top 5): {events_json}
Restaurants nearby: {restaurants_json}
Transit: {transit_json}
Property notes: {property_notes}

Return JSON:
{
  "greeting": "string (1 sentence, warm)",
  "weather_summary": "string (≤40 words)",
  "packing_tips": ["string", ...] (3 tips),
  "events": [{"name", "date", "type", "why_youll_love_it"}] (top 3),
  "dining": [{"name", "cuisine", "dietary_match", "note"}] (top 3),
  "transit": "string (≤60 words)",
  "property_note": "string (≤40 words)"
}
```

## Mock Fallback
When `USE_MOCK_LLM=true`, return a pre-built fixture for each persona from
`/data/seeds/arrival_brief_{persona_id}.json`. Always have mock data for Alex, Jordan, Sam.

## Consent & Privacy
- Toggle lives in `/profile` → "Arrival Brief" switch
- Stored in guest profile as `preferences.arrival_brief_enabled: bool`
- If disabled, do not generate or show the brief — show a "Re-enable in Settings" placeholder instead
- No external data sent except: city name + check-in date to weather API (no PII)

## Components
- `ArrivalBriefCard` — teaser card in My Stays view (appears 48h before check-in)
- `ArrivalBriefPage` — full brief at `/arrival-brief/:stay_id`
- `WeatherWidget` — 3-day strip (icon, high/low temp)
- `BriefSection` — reusable: icon + heading + content
- `DietaryFilterBadge` — "Filtered for: Vegetarian" pill shown on dining section
- `ConsentToggleRow` — in profile settings page

## API Endpoint
`GET /stays/{stay_id}/arrival-brief` → triggers brief generation (or returns cached)
`POST /stays/{stay_id}/arrival-brief/refresh` → forces regeneration
